Light Strength Tuning The delicacy and solidness of prints is determined by the strength of laser beam. You may adjust the strength of laser power based on common features and purpose of your prints. The printer prints with moderate laser power by default. You may get more delicate objects when printing with lower laser power, but the printouts may slightly weak under force. If the objects deform easily, you may try to increase the laser power. For current room temperature The printer prints in moderate laser power by default. You may adjust the settings by following the suggested value for different temperature segments. The setting will affect the delicacy and solidness of prints. Printing with lower laser power will result in finer details. However, if the objects deform easily, you may try to increasing the laser power. The printer firmware has been updated. Cone Tree Contact area Top Diameter Base Diameter Trunk Branch Height Structure Selected structure: Low High Done Single branch Multi branch How to use:
Step 1: Set up cone mark (orange dot) • Add cone mark: click on the overhangs on the model to add cone marks. • Delete cone mark: click on the orange mark to remove.
Step 2: Generate cone structure • Generate cone: click "Generate" after setting up cone marks.
Note: 1. Cone support is only available when the overhang is at least 6mm above the platform. %software_name% will lift the object when necessary. 2. The base diameter of the support should be at least 1mm larger then the top diameter. Please set up the bottom diameter first then the top diameter. 3. The diameter of the support can't be changed once added. To adjust the support, please delete the mark, change the diameters and add the cone mark again.
1. Setting up the trunk (thick yellow stick) Add trunk: click on the desired location on the platform. Move trunk: click on the trunk and hold to drop. Delete trunk: click on the trunk to delete it.
Note: The trunk with no branch will be deleted when generating.
Setting up the branch Step 1: Select a trunk to add branches •Select a trunk: click on the trunk to turn it into blue.
Step 2: Set up branch mark (thin yellow stick) •Add a branch: click on the model. •Delete a branch: click on the thin stick to delete it.
Step 3: Complete your tree •Click "Generate" after setting up all marks.
Note: 1. When no trunk is selected, the branch will be shown as a yellow dot. Simply click on a trunk, the branch mark will be connected to the selected trunk. 2. Branch mark should be higher than the top of the selected trunk. 3. Branch mark is disabled when no trunk is available.
Generate tree supports After setting up the trunk and branches, click "Generate" to apply the settings.
Note: 1. Branches over 45 degree slope will be shown in red, as they may be displaced in the printing process. 2. Trunk with no branch connected will be deleted while generating the supports.
1. Click on the targeted cone (selected cone will change to blue). 2. Drag the slider to adjust the contact area. 3. Click "Done" once you have adjusted the contact area of all cones.
Step 1: Select the branch Select a single branch: click on the branch. Select all branched of the same trunk: click on the trunk.
Step 2: Adjust the contact area •Drag the slider to adjust the contact area.
